<HEADLINE> Lesotho to Set Up Independent Electoral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Lesotho National Assembly
today approved legislation which provides for the establishment of an
independent electoral commission before the general election scheduled
for January next year.
</P>
<P>
Under the the new legislation, the independent electoral commission
will be responsible for all essential electoral management tasks,
including deliminatation of constituencies, registration of voters,
polling and counting.
</P>
<P>
The commission will also take measures to popularize public
eduction on democracy and elections, according to informed sources
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the new law also lowers to 18 the age of citizens
allowed to vote from 21.
</P>
<P>
The first democratic elections were held in 1993 when the
ruling Basutholand Congress Party took all the 65 seats in the
National Assembly. enditem

