<HEADLINE> Qiqihar Wins National Ice Hockey Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JILIN, northeastern China, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Qiqihar
Black Dragons won the Chinese Ice Hockey Championship after
eight-day competition here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The undefeated Black Dragons chalked six wins in the
round-robin tournament, which pitted seven teams against each
other.
</P>
<P>
Jilin finished second with one loss and five victories,
including the key win against third-placed Harbin which boasted
nine national team members. 
</P>
