<HEADLINE> Bank Gives Loans to Three State Firms in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) and three state-owned enterprises in East
China's Jiangsu Province signed agreements here today to set up
cooperative ties between the bank and the firms.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, ICBC's local branches will provide loans
totaling 2.49 billion yuan to the Yizheng Chemical Fiber Company,
Chunhua Group and Yangtze Petrochemical Company.
</P>
<P>
All the three firms play a big role in their respective
fields. In 1996, they generated 21.7 billion yuan in output value
and 1.83 billion yuan in profit. By the end of 1996, their total
assets reached 33.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the bank had lent 2.55 billion yuan in
loans to the three companies.
</P>
<P>
ICBC is currently taking measures to establish a new
relationship with enterprises and to provide an overall service to
the firms regarding accounting, payment, clearance and
information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
