<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, US Cooperate On Children's Environmental Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States are
working together on an education project aimed to foster
environmental awareness among children and young people in China.
</P>
<P>
Beginning today, which is the twenty-eighth "Earth Day,"
teachers from 20 of the country's primary and middle schools will
attend a one-week workshop in Beijing, featuring lectures by US
environmental experts.
</P>
<P>
The teachers in turn are asked to present the information to
their colleagues and students back home.
</P>
<P>
The lectures are meant to instruct youngsters on how to observe
and measure local air temperature, precipitation, water surface
temperature and the ecological situation.
</P>
<P>
The children will be provided with environmental observation
equipment, and the data they collect will be sent via Internet to
a processing center in Boulder, Colorado of the US, where it will
be re-created into colorful pictures illustrating the global
environmental situation.
</P>
<P>
Officials here said the project will help the youngsters not
only to gain a better understanding of the environment in their
localities, but also help them recognize the changes that occur in
the global environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
