<HEADLINE> Jordan's Crown Prince Urges Doubling Efforts for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan
today called for doubling efforts to overcome the obstacles facing
the Middle East peace process in order to achieve a comprehensive
and just peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with a military delegation of the Pakistani Defense
Academy, Crown Prince Hassan underscored Jordan's unqualified
support for the Palestinian people in their struggle for the
establishment of the independent state on their own soil and to
exercise their legitimate rights.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian news agency Petra quoted Hassan as underlining
the illegality for Israel to build the Jewish settlements in the
occupied Palestinian territories, including Jerusalem, noting
such an action would inflict damages on the regional peace process.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the necessity of building comprehensive regional
security that takes into consideration the social and economic
dimensions, indicating the importance of regional cooperation in
dealing with issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli peace talks were stalled over a month
since Israel decided on April 18 to press ahead with a Jewish
neighborhood in Arab East Jerusalem despite international
objection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
