<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Council Issues Decree on PBOC Currency Policy Board </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng signed a State
Council decree today to issue the "Regulations on the Currency
Policy Committee of the People's Bank of China."
</P>
<P>
Under the regulations, which went into effect today, the
currency policy committee acts as a consultant to China's central
bank.
</P>
<P>
The committee has the obligation to discuss matters regarding
the formulation and readjustment of currency policy, the currency
policy targets within a certain period, the utilization of policy
tools, important measures concerning the policy, and the
coordination between currency policy and other macro-economic
control policies, according to the new rules.
</P>
<P>
The board is composed of the PBOC governor and two deputy
governors as well as several vice ministers and senior officials
from the State Planning Commission, the State Economic and Trade
Commission, the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of
Foreign Exchange, and the China Securities Regulatory Commission.
</P>
<P>
Presidents from two solely state-owned commercial banks and a
banking expert will also be included on the board, according to
the regulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
