<HEADLINE> Seminar on Implementation of International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) and the International Committee of the Red Cross
(ICRC) will jointly organize a seminar on the implementation of
international humanitarian law here on April 29-30.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Zidane Meriboute, Head of the ICRC
mission to the OAU, at a press briefing here today.
</P>
<P>
Meriboute said African ambassadors accredited to the OAU,
ambassadors from the members of the UN Security Council and the
Council of Europe will attend the two-day seminar.
</P>
<P>
Meriboute said the seminar will be lectured by Judge Richard
Goldstone, former Chief Prosecutor of Ttribunal Ex-Yugoslavia and
Arusha; Kama, President of the International Criminal Tribunal
for Rwanda; Ahmed Mahiou, President of the UN International Law
Commission; and Toni Pfanner, Head of the Lagal Division of the
ICRC.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is the fourth one jointly organized by the OAU and
the ICRC.
</P>
<P>
According to the ICRC, the International Humanitarian Law,
also called the law of war, sets out detailed rules which seek to
limit the effect of armed conflict. In particular, it protects
those who are not, or are no longer, taking part in the fighting,
and sets limits on the means and methods of warfare. enditem

