<HEADLINE> S. Africa Has No Plan to Evacuate Staff from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has no plan to
evacuate its staff from the war-torn Zaire, Deputy Foreign
Minister Aziz Pahad said in Cape Town today.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to media reports that South Africans were being evacuated
from Zaire, Pahad told the National Assembly Foreign Affairs Committee
"we have no plan to evacuate our staff. They will remain."
</P>
<P>
