<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, ICIPE Sign Memorandum of Understanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A memorandum of understanding
was signed here today between China and the International Center
of Insect Physiology and Ecology (ICIPE) for scientific research
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to the memorandum, the two sides will cooperate in
scientific researches and training in the management of pests and
natural resources in China and African countries.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to establish scientific cooperation and to
conduct joint researches and training in mutually agreed specific
areas.
</P>
<P>
China and ICIPE also agreed to exchange scientists and
scientific information to facilitate their cooperation, and
to jointly organize workshops and seminars on research projects.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum was signed by Yang Yansheng, Vice-President of
the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences (CAAS), and ICIPE
Director General Hans R. Herren.
</P>
<P>
ICIPE is an international institute whose research is directed
toward contributing to the development of sustainable management
of arthropod pests and improved utilization of beneficial ones.
</P>
<P>
The insect center is also designed to strengthen scientific
and technological capacities of the developing countries in
arthropod science and its application through training and
collaborative work.
</P>
<P>
And, the CAAS is the national agricultural research
organization affiliated to the Ministry of Agriculture of the
People's Republic of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
