<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Warns Against Political Thuggery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The West African peacekeeping
force (ECOMOG) today warned against harassment and thuggery
during campaigning in the war-ravaged Liberia, emphasizing that
violators would be punished.
</P>
<P>
The ECOMOG said in a statement that it "wishes to warn that no
acts of intimidation, coercion, incitement, harassment and thuggery
would be tolerated from any of the political parties or their
supporters."
</P>
<P>
It said that "peace and security are the most vital elements for
the holding of a free and fair election, as envisaged by the ECOWAS
authorities and this we promise to maintain."
</P>
<P>
"ECOMOG has received reports of some unscrupulous partisans
intimidating supporters of other parties, while they were also
intimidating returning refugees with the aim of coercing them to join
their parties," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It therefore warned that any party, group of persons under the name
of a party caught intimidating supporters of other parties or
returning refugees would be accordingly penalized.  
</P>
</TEXT>
