<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Web Site Going into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The China Wide Web network today
launched its first broadcast of the Hong Kong 1997 Web Site, the
result of a global multi-media partnership, at a special ceremony
in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Editorial content for the site, which was officially kicked off
in Hong Kong last week, has been contributed by the Xinhua News
Agency, which has provided the Web Site with a comprehensive
review of Hong Kong, including information about its history, and
current and upcoming events.
</P>
<P>
A section featuring the pictorial history of Hong Kong is also
included, with some historical archive photographs available to
the public for the first time.
</P>
<P>
As world attention focuses on Hong Kong in the weeks prior to
China's resumption of sovereignty over it on July 1, the Web Site
will provide a comprehensive and up-to-the minute handover news
and photo service.
</P>
<P>
The China Wide Web network is jointly developed by the China
Economic Information Service of the Xinhua News Agency and the
Hong Kong-based China Internet Corporation (CIC). 
</P>
</TEXT>
