<DOCNO> XIE19970423.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Newspapers Welcome Jiang's Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Major Russian newspapers have
greeted Chinese President Jiang Zemin's arrival here today with
reports and articles welcoming his state visit.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's visit, scheduled to last five days, is an important
event, Russia's Deputy Foreign Minister Grigori Karasin was quoted
as saying by a report in today's daily Komsomol Pravda.
</P>
<P>
"Russia has long given a priority to the relations with China,
and this has nothing to do with developments in Europe, such as
NATO's proposed eastward expansion," Karasin said.
</P>
<P>
On border issues, he said Russia will honor its promise by
working with China to finish the demarcation of the eastern
section of the Sino-Russia common border within this year.
</P>
<P>
It is an undertaking in the interest of both countries and with
strategic importance, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russia's ambassador to China Igor Alexeyevich
Rogachev said in an interview with the daily Trud that "Moscow and
Beijing both favor dialogues at the highest level."
</P>
<P>
Jiang's visit is "of particular significance not only for
bilateral ties, but also for the peace and stability of
the Asia-Pacific region and the entire world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rogachev also paid great tribute to a document to be signed
during Jiang's visit, saying it "will make the 7,500-kilometer
common border a belt of peace and stability in Asia."
</P>
<P>
The treaty, to be signed by China, Russia, and former Soviet
republics of Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan, will call for
further reduction of military presence along border areas.
</P>
<P>
China has mutual borders with Russia and the three Central
Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Rogachev pointed out that the partnership between
Russia and China based on mutual trust in politics will serve as a
locomotive for promoting bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Sergei Mikhailovich Shakhrai, Russia's presidential
representative to the Constitutional Court, wrote an article in
today's the Independent Newspaper about China's experience in
economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
He said reformers in Russia should learn the successful
experience from the East as well as the West.
</P>
<P>
Europe and America do not know what is socialist economy, he
noted. China, however, has been upholding socialism while
successfully undertaking market-oriented economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
It is now the best time to push forward the development of
relations between Russia and China, he concluded.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here on Tuesday for his fourth official summit
with Russian President Boris Yeltsin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
