<HEADLINE> WEC Forum on New Energy Technology Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Several hundred officials and
energy experts from around the world attended today's opening
ceremony in Beijing of the World Energy Council (WEC) Asia Pacific
Regional Forum, to discuss new energy technology for the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Participants from 25 countries and regions were at the event,
held at the Shangri-la Hotel.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the meeting is to study new policies on energy
development in the Asia-Pacific region and promote regional
cooperation in energy utilization and development.
</P>
<P>
The forum will convene five panel discussions, covering
potential cooperative projects in the fields of coal, electricity,
oil and gas, renewable energy and fund-raising.
</P>
<P>
In his speach at today's event, Ye Qing, vice minister of the
State Planning Commission, welcomed energy specialists from all
over the world to the Chinese capital to talk about major energy
issues.
</P>
<P>
Development of new energy is conducive to economic development
and serves as a guarantee for a sustained development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Toyoaki Ikuta, president of the WEC Asia Pacific Regional
Forum, said in a speech that in Asia, East Asia in particular, a
rapid increase in energy demand is expected to occur as a result
of substantial economic growth.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out, energy production is unable to meet
this precipitous growth demand. Therefore, the dependence on
energy imports, especially on oil from the Middle East, will
increase.
</P>
<P>
Taking proper action to ensure energy security is of vital
importance in solving energy and environmental issues, not only in
this region but for the entire world, he said, adding that this
may well be a major challenge early in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that all those present will be able to do
more to solve the energy issue in this region by specifically
detailing problems and distributing all information to the member
nations for discussion.
</P>
<P>
The WEC was founded in 1923 and has over the years become the
world's leading non-governmental energy policy forum whose
objective is to promote the sustainable supply and use of energy
for the greatest benefit of all. It has member committees in 100
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
