<HEADLINE> Australian Prime Minister Meets Ding Guangen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Australian Prime Minister John
Winston Howard met here today with Ding Guangen, member of the
Political Bureau and the Secretariat of the Communist Party of
China.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, Ding conveyed Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and Premier Li Peng's greetings to Howard and extended
congratulations for the later's recent and successful visit to
China.
</P>
<P>
Howard said he welcomed Ding's visit to Australia.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Chinese leaders for their warm reception during his
China tour, which achieved positive results, and expressed the
hope that the bilateral ties would be further promoted.
</P>
<P>
In this afternoon, Australian Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister for Trade Tim Fischer, Foreign Minister Alexander Downer,
Minister for Communication and the Arts Richard Alston also met
Ding, respectively, to discuss the development of friendly
relations between the two governments and peoples, and the
promotion of trade cooperation and cultural exchanges between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ding arrived in Australia on April 19 for a goodwill visit at
the invitation of the Australian Federal Government. 
</P>
