<HEADLINE> Illegal Immigrants Arrested in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Greek police today arrested a
large number of Albanians and Iraqis for illegally entering the
country.
</P>
<P>
According to the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) today,
a total of 209 illegal immigrants from Albania have been arrested
and deported over the past 24 hours in the Greek prefecture of
Epirus, which borders on Albania.
</P>
<P>
Of them, a truck carrying 93 Albanians was stopped by Greek
police near Drosopighes, Konitsa, this morning.
</P>
<P>
The driver managed to escape, but police arrested his
accomplice, who said that the two had been paid 65,000 drachma
(about 250 U.S. dollars) from each Albanian to take them from the
border to the Greek capital of Athens.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 57 Iraqis were arrested by a Greek army patrol this
morning on the islet of Farmakonisi, in the eastern Dodecanese.
</P>
</TEXT>
