<HEADLINE> 34 Foreigners Caught in Somalia for Illegal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mogadishu, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A large vessel with 34
foreigners has been caught fishing on the sea shores of Mudug
region, 600 km north of here.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters here today, Ali Abdulle Osman, the
Chairman of Gara Ad Village on the shores, said the ship was
caught by four armed speed boats off the sea shore and brought
forcefully to anchor at nearby port two days ago.
</P>
<P>
Some of the occupants of the vessel including the captain
were brought to Jarriban town 10 km west of the village for
questioning, he said.
</P>
<P>
The crew men caught in the fishing vessel are Italians,
Kenyans, Romanians and Somalis, according to Osman.
</P>
<P>
The vessel, Bahari Hindi, owned by an Italian company,
Marabasha, flew a Kenyan national flag and sailed from Mombasa of
Kenya, he said. enditem

