<HEADLINE> Palestinian Airliners to Take Off From Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian airliners will take off
from the airport of the Egyptian Mediterranean port city of Al
Arish temporarily and fly to a number of airports in neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Palestinian Aviation Authority Fayez Zeidan said
today that the temporary arrangement through Al Arish airport will
continue until Gaza airport begins to operate, the Egyptian MENA
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
MENA quoted sources from Amman as saying Palestinian passenger
planes will land in Cairo, Amman, Cyprus, Jeddah and Istanbul
airports.
</P>
<P>
The opening of Gaza airport remains one of the pending issues
in the stalled Palestinian-Israeli talks. 
</P>
