<HEADLINE> S. Africa Makes Tourism Development Action Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A toruism development action
plan aimed at creating 310,000 new jobs in the sector by the year 2000
was being finalized, Environment and Tourism Minister Pallo Jordan
said today.
</P>
<P>
The plan aimed to increase the tourism industry's share of gross
domestic product from the current four percent to eight percent by
the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
It also aimed at increasing the number of overseas tourists
visiting South Africa by six percent a year to 4.8 million, South
African Press Association (SAPA) quoted Jordan as reporting.
</P>
<P>
Following the implementation of the plan, Jordan said, there would
be more sustainable employment opportunities in the sector from
550,000 to 860,000.
</P>
<P>
SAPA reported that work on the plan had already commenced, with the
new South Africa Tourism Board having been elected and a task group to
address safety and security for tourists having been formed. enditem

