<HEADLINE> Nigeria Maps out New Defense Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A 16-member committee today mapped
out Nigeria's defense policy by the year 2000, according to the
official News Agency of Nigeria (NAN).
</P>
<P>
Chief of Defense Staff, Major-General Abudulsallam Abubarkar,
upon receiving the report from a 16-member committee, said it
will be handed over to Head of State General Sani Abacha for
"necessary action". However, contents of the defense policy was
not known.
</P>
<P>
Air Vice-Marshal Al-Ammin Daggash, chairman of the committee,
told NAN that the report has taken into consideration of the
global geo-political situation, "especially Nigeria's centralized
position in the continent."
</P>
<P>
The committee was set up in July last year to review Nigeria's
defense policy in view of developments in the strategic global
environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
