<HEADLINE> Fire Breaks Out on Two Ships in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Fire broke out this morning on two
ships docking for repairs in Greece, leaving one person dead and
causing extensive damage to the ships.
</P>
<P>
Local police said that the blaze started during metalsheet
repairs on the 12,067dwt Cyprus-flagged cargo ship, the Ionian
Bridge, which docked for repairs at a shipyard in Perama, near the
port of Piraeus, about 15 kilometers southwest of Athens.
</P>
<P>
A 40-year-old worker died on the way to hospital from severe
burns.
</P>
<P>
The 21-member crew on board the ship, all Greeks, escaped
unhurt and the fire had been brought under control after causing
extensive damage.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another fire which broke out on board the 37,277dwt
Panamanian freighter, the Minoan Hill, was also brought under
control, causing damage but without any injuries, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian freighter docked for repairs at Drapetsona, near
the port of Piraeus. 
