<HEADLINE> Annan Stresses Information's Social Impact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General Kofi
Annan said that it was necessary to see that the free flow of
information truly worked to make people live in larger freedom and
greater prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In a message to a roundtable assessing the impact of
globalization of information, he noted that new technologies were
empowering community and civic action groups around the world and
providing new channels by which the United Nations could reach out
to vast numbers of people in efforts to build a better world.
</P>
<P>
The four-day roundtable, which opened Monday and will conclude
Thursday, is being attended by 40 senior media practitioners,
industry representatives, academics and UN officials. It is
organized by the the UN Department of Public Information and the
Columbia University School of International and Public Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Discussions emphasized the need to broaden international access
to new communications technologies and looked into ways and means
of how these technologies can help promote sustainable human
development. 
