<HEADLINE> Egyptian Policeman Killed in clash with Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A secret force policeman was killed
and six others wounded during an exchange of fires with suspected
militants early this morning, said a source at the Interior
Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The source noted that the police headed for the a village in
Samalout, Manya, 120 kilometers south of Cairo, after they were
tipped at around 02:00 local time (midnight GMT) that suspects in
the slaying of a Christian farmer were gathering there.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged fires as the policemen try to arrest
the assailants, who were believed behind the killing of Istefanos
Zaki, a Coptic Christian farmer whose body was found Monday on his
wheat farm.
</P>
<P>
Minya security bodies rushed to the scene immediately after the
shooting and cordoned off the area to hunt for the culprits, the
source said.
</P>
<P>
While combing the area for the fugitives today, the security
forces also hit upon the body of another slain policeman in nearby
wheat plantations.
</P>
<P>
Coptic Christians, who constitute about 10 percent of Egypt's
63 million people, have been the targets of terrorist attacks of
Islamic militants who regard them as pagans.
</P>
<P>
Today's killing occurred only two days after another terrorist
attack, in which two police officers were killed and four others
wounded in the southern province of Assuit, 360 kilometers south
of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,168 people have been killed since the start of a
five-year anti-government militant campaign aimed to set up a
strict Islamic rule in Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
