<HEADLINE> 19 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces struck
heavy blows against the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in
southeastern Turkey during the Feast of the Sacrifice holiday and
shot dead 19 PKK rebels, an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that in operations to clear the PKK militants from the
region, the Turkish security forces killed eight rebels near
Bingol province, six in Cemisgezek town of Tunceli province and
five in Gulluce mountain region of Sirnak province bordering
northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
One PKK guerrilla surrendered to the government troops in Eruh
town of Siirt province, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The Agency said that a group of PKK rebels in the southeastern
town of Genc attacked a security team which was patrolling the
area and seriously injured three soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Another PKK group wounded two members of government special
teams in an attack on a police station in Alacakaya near Elazig
province, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 12-year-old separatist war which
has claimed over 21,000 lives in the east and the southeast of
Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
