<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-22 20:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Seeks Foreign Investments in Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Egypt is seeking more
international investments on expansion of the current living
areas, Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal el Ganzouri said here today.
</P>
<P>
Egypt needs new capital not only from the Arab world, but also
from other foreign investors, Ganzouri told reporters after a
close-door meeting with President of the United Arab Emirates(UAE)
Sheikh Sayed al Nahayyan.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian prime minister made a brief stop-over here after
an Asian tour this month, which has taken him to Malaysia,
Singapore and China.
</P>
<P>
Ganzouri said Egypt has mapped out a plan to expand the living
areas by five times of the current level, which now stands at some
55,000 square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The current living areas in Egypt is mainly located at the Nile
Valley, which represented only 5.5 percent of the total territory,
but with more than 90 percent of the population of the country.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of new living areas has turned an "imminent
issue" for Egypt because of an explosion of the population, which
has reached some 60.28 million now, three times of that 50 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
"Our guideline for the land expansion to the outside of
the valley has turned an imminent issue," Ganzouri said.
</P>
<P>
The land expansion is mainly focused on the north of
the Suez Gulf and the southern Nile Valley, Ganzouri added. He
gave no details about investment projects in these areas.
</P>
<P>
However, Ganzouri said that the investment projects will
benefit both Egyptians and investors.
</P>
<P>
Observers noted that since Egypt adopted the open-door policy
in 1981, it has successfully obtained 15.47 billion U.S. dollars
for 5,384 investment projects set up in the past 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia is the biggest investor in Egypt, followed by
Kuwait and UAE. The UAE has contributed to 73 investment projects
in Egypt. It also provide Egypt financial assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
