<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, April 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin and his
Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin signed a joint statement here on
Wednesday, pledging to strive for promoting the multipolarization
of the world and the establishment of a new world order.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Wednesday
that efforts by China and Russia's top legislatures have
contributed to the smooth development of the two countries'
relations. Jiang made the remarks while meeting Gennady Seleznev,
speaker of the State Duma, the lower house of Russian parliament,
and leaders of major parties in the Duma.
</P>
