AMMAN -- King Hussein of Jordan and Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) President Yasser Arafat met in the southern
Jordanian city of Aqaba Wednesday to discuss the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- Peruvian armed forces stormed Japanese Ambassador
Morihisa Aoki's residence in Lima on Tuesday afternoon, ending a
four-month-long hostage crisis.
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japanese Foreign Minister Yukihiko Ikeda left Tokyo
for Lima on Wednesday to convey Japan's gratitude to the Peruvian
government over ending the four-month-long hostage crisis at the
Japanese ambassador's residence.
</P>
<P>
BONN -- The German government and the main opposition party in
Bonn said they have failed to strike a compromise on a government
plan to overhaul the country taxation system. Chancellor Helmut
Kohl and Oskar Lafontaine, leader of the main opposition Social
Democratic Party (SPD) met for only one hour Wednesday in Bonn
before announcing the failure of negotiations which began in
February.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Russian
President Boris Yeltsin Wednesday announced the official
establishment of the Sino-Russian Friendship Committee for Peace
and Development. 
</P>
