<HEADLINE> Northwest China Expects Large Oil field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Major breakthroughs have been
achieved in the oil and gas exploration in the eastern parts of
the Junggar Basin in Xinjiang, and the birth of a
hundred-million-ton oilfield is expected.
</P>
<P>
The Xinjiang Oil Administration announced here today that the
new-found oilfield is located in Shaqiuhe region, about 130 km
from Urumqi, capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The administration drilled a test well in the area in April,
and high-quality petroleum associated with gas was found above the
underground level of 1,805 meters.
</P>
<P>
Tests of the gas proves that the well is the first high-yield
exploratory well found on China's mainland so far this year, and
gas can be found in an area of 84 sq km around the area.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the area is one of the important rich
oilfields in the east Junggar Basin, with its geological reserve
of oil and natural gas hitting about 100 million tons of oil.
</P>
<P>
Several oilfields have been found in the eastern parts of the
basin, with a total petroleum reserve of 200 million tons. The
area turned out 2.12 million tons of crude oil last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
