He noted that the target date of this weekend for the
submission of the bill on the use of flag and emblem in the HKSAR
had been made on the basis of a very preliminary forecast of
business.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the target has become unachievable due to
pressures on the office from other fronts and considerations of
issues that have arisen in the course of preparing the bill in
question.
</P>
<P>
"We are doing the best we can with our limited resources," he
said. "We are firmly committed to completing the drafting of all
essential bills in good time for their passage by the PLC before
July 1." 
