<DOCNO> XIE19970423.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on New Manufacturing Network Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on establishing a
network in Asia to enhance the competitiveness of manufacturing
industry of Hong Kong and the Chinese mainland opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Polytechnic University, the two-day
seminar will examine the level of effective use of both product
design capabilities and manufacturing resources in the Chinese
mainland and the Asian region.
</P>
<P>
About 20 renowned academics from universities in the Chinese
mainland attended the seminar, including presidents and professors
from the Zhejiang University, the Harbin Institute of Technology,
the Beijing University of Science and Technology, the Tongji
University, the Chinese academy of Engineering, Shenyang Institute
of Computing Technology.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the organizer for the seminar said that through
regional and international networking, all functions related to
manufacturing, such as product design and development or
marketing, can be done in different regions around the world where
talent and resources are available at the lowest costs.
</P>
<P>
He said that the advancement of telecommunications technology
has made possible the formation of virtual manufacturing
enterprises through computer networks to tap into the dispersed
global resources.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, a central focus of the seminar will
be to discuss the feasibility of establishing a Dispersed Network
Production System (DNPS) in Hong Kong and in the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
It is hoped that the DNPS will give Hong Kong and the Chinese
mainland an edge over others in serving as the Asia-Pacific
manufacturing network center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
