<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Indonesia Sign Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Indonesia today
signed a memorandum of understanding on bilateral discussions
and contacts and an agreement to avoid double taxation.
</P>
<P>
The two accords were separately signed by the Indonesian
Foreign Minister Ali Abdullah Alatas with Kuwaiti Acting Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmed Al-Jaber
Al-Sabah and Kuwaiti Finance Minister Nasser Abdullah Al-Rudhan
during Alatas' two-day visit here.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Alatas, who arrived here Tuesday, also held
talks with Kuwaiti officials aimed at boosting bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Kuwaiti Foreign Ministry said Sheikh
Sabah and Alatas discussed ways to promote bilateral relations
in all fields, especially in the economic sector.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Sabah and Alatas also discussed a number of regional
and international issues of common concern, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Alatas also invited the acting premier to visit Indonesia
soon.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Alatas was received by Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh
Jaber al-Ahmed al-Sabah and conveyed a message from Indonesian
President Suharto to the Amir.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Indonesia are considering to open a new air route
to the Indonesian island of Bali to expand commercial
cooperation on airways between the two countries and meet the
increasing demands of exchanges in various fields between
them. 
</P>
