<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets International Celebrities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren
met here today with former Canadian Prime Minister Martin Brian
Mulroney, former US Secretary of State George Shultz and other
international dignitaries who are in China to attend the second
session of the China International Trust and Investment
Corp.(CITIC) International Advisory Council.
</P>
<P>
Other well-known guests to attend tomorrow's meeting are from
political and business circles of the US, Britain, Japan,
Netherlands, Australia, Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
In his welcoming address to the group, Rong said that he hopes
the guests will offer suggestions for China's economic development
and financial reform.
</P>
<P>
Rong said he is convinced that CITIC will make rapid progress
with the help of the council members.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the guests on China's economic development, Rong
attributed the country's continuous, rapid and healthy development
and the effective curbing of inflation to following the socialist
road with Chinese characteristics initiated by late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping, upholding the policy of reform and opening and
effectively promoting international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China's development still has a long way to go, Rong said, but
China believes that with its own efforts and international
assistance, the outlook is bright.
</P>
<P>
Mulroney said that all of the council members felt free to
speak out on the theme of the session.
</P>
<P>
And Shultz noted that everyone who has an interest in economic
issues is attentive to China's economic development.
</P>
<P>
CITIC, established in 1979, has become a comprehensive
transnational industries group. CITIC International Advisory
Council was set up in 1995 to bring about further expansion of
business, and 13 international figures such as Mulroney and Shultz
were invited to be members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
