<HEADLINE> Bundesbank Predicts Sustained Recovery of German Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Germany's central bank said today it
expected the country's economic recovery to sustain with the
support of strong exports.
</P>
<P>
The Bundesbank said in a report that foreign orders in the
first two months this year rose by a real 12 percent while
domestic orders increased by only one percent.
</P>
<P>
Normalized exchange rates, low interest rates and moderate wage
increases would also contribute to the economic upturn, it added.
</P>
<P>
However, the expected economic recovery would not help improve
unemployment.
</P>
<P>
It called again for further reduction in government spending to
meet the Maastricht Treaty budget deficit criteria set for joining
the European single currency, the Euro.
</P>
<P>
This is important for improving conditions for economic growth
and for employment in the country, it said. 
</P>
