<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Park's Double Gives South Korea Win over China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- One header in each half from Park
Kun Ha boosted South Korea to a 2-0 victory over host China in a
soccer friendly here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China pounded South Korean goal almost constantly from the
start in the first half but failed to find a way to beat keeper
Kim Bong Soo.
</P>
<P>
In a dazzling fast counter-attack in the 45th minute, Park Kun
Ha received a long pass from a teammate and headed the ball past
Chinese goalie Ou Chuliang.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese mounted all-out attacks after break and had several
scoring chances.
</P>
<P>
But South Korea surged to a 2-0 lead in the 57th minute, when a
South Korean shot hitting the bar of the goal sent the ball just
in front of Park.
</P>
<P>
Park sprinted ahead to head the ball, which bounced on the
ground and flew high over Ou's reaching hands into the net.
</P>
<P>
The game was one of three warm-ups in eight days for China,
which is preparing for the coming World Cup Asian Zone group 8
qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese eleven beat Myanmar 5-0 here on Sunday and will
face Iran next Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
