<HEADLINE> Pak Government to Present Budget for 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's national budget for
the 1997-98 fiscal year will be presented on June 14 with special
emphasis on structural adjustments and economic stabilization.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the budget, to be presented by Finance
Minister Sartaj Aziz, entered a crucial phase following an
expected shortfall in the revenue collection to the tune of 40
billion rupees (about 1 billion U.S. dollars) during the current
fiscal year ending on June 30, according to a report by the
Associated Press of Pakistan today.
</P>
<P>
The Executive Committee of the National Economic Council is
scheduled to hold a meeting to be chaired by Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif next month to review the draft budget for 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
Consultations with the business and traders' community and
their chambers and associations are being held with the economic
managers and financial experts of the government.
</P>
<P>
The government Priorities Committee is meeting regularly to
carve out a draft reflecting the economic targets and objectives
of the government to transform the economic fabric of the country.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
