<HEADLINE> British Expedition Team Leader Dies on Mount Qomolangma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Malcolm Duff, team leader of an
eight-member British expedition team, has died at basecamp before
the team attempted to climb Mount Qomolangma, the Nepalese tourism
ministry announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The cause of death of Duff, 44, was not immediately known, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
"Malcolm had gone to his tent at the basecamp, situated at the
height of 5,300 meters, Tuesday night but the next morning he was
found dead in his tent," it said.
</P>
<P>
The death occurred before the start of the expedition's attempt
to scale Mount Qomolangma, the world's highest mountain at 8,848
meters.
</P>
<P>
British team members were arranging to transport the body back
to Kathmandu so it could be flown back to Britain, a tourism
official said.
</P>
<P>
The team had not immediately decided whether to continue its
climb, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
