<HEADLINE> Singapore Police Arrest 4 for Alleged Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Four Singaporeans, including a
15-year-old middle school girl, were arrested by the Central
Narcotics Bureau (CNB) officers for allegedly joint trafficking in
1.609 kilograms of heroin, local television reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that acting on a tip-off, the CNB officers arrested a
25-year-old man who was leaving a flat of a residential building
in the central part of the country and recovered a white envelope
containing five sachets of heroin.
</P>
<P>
The officers then raided the flat and two unemployed men aged
27 and 24 years and a 15-year-old school girl were detained.
</P>
<P>
In the one-room flat, the officers allegedly recovered two
packets, 114 sachets and 25 straws of heroin weighing a total
1.609 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Also seized were 9,566 Singapore dollars (about 6643 US
dollars) in cash, a sealing machine, an electronic digital
weighing scale and a bundle of empty plastic bags.
</P>
<P>
The four persons will be charged in court with joint drug
trafficking on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the laws of Singapore, if the net weight of the heroin is
found to exceed 15 grams, the three men will face the death
penalty if convicted.
</P>
<P>
The girl, being below 18 years old, will be detained at the
President's pleasure, the television report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
