<HEADLINE> 19th International Children's Day Observed in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The 19th International
Children's Day is being warmly celebrated today in the whole
Turkey as well as in Turkey's embassies abroad.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of lovely children from 38 countries, including
China, Egypt, Nigeria, Germany, Indonesia, have been attending
one-week-long holiday celebrations organized by the Turkish Radio
and Television (TRT).
</P>
<P>
They have made all kinds of shows in Ankara, capital of
Turkey, in a bid to develop the existing friendly ties between
Turkey and their countries.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with representatives from the 38 countries in
the presidential palace here this morning, Turkish President
Suleyman Demirel said: "You are the future of your countries,
but all of you are the future of humanity. We love all of you."
</P>
<P>
He said that the future world will be the peace world, and
people in the whole world will live without any fear or anxiety.
</P>
<P>
Demirel received the gifts from the 38 countries and also
gave pens engraved with his signature name as presents to
the representatives.
</P>
<P>
At his meeting with children representatives from the 38
countries today, Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan, who
just returned from pilgrimage in Mecca, Saudi Arabia, said: "To
educate our children is peace and brotherhood in the world."
</P>
<P>
Erbakan also sent watches and pens as gifts to the
representatives of the foreign countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
