<HEADLINE> Ramos Lauds Fujimori for Ending Peru Hostage Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today joined world leaders in congratulating Peruvian President
Alberto Fujimori for the successful end of a four-month-old
hostage crisis in Lima.
</P>
<P>
The president said during his weekly press conference that the
Filipino people are deeply relieved that the suffering of the
hostages and their families is now over.
</P>
<P>
"I am pleased to convey to your excellency my most sincere
congratulations for the successful termination of the hostage
crisis at the residence of the Japanese ambassador in Lima," Ramos
also said in a letter to Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
In a daylight assault Tuesday, Peruvian government commandos
set free 71 hostages held by a guerrilla group at the Japanese
ambassador's residence since December 17.
</P>
<P>
Ramos praised the Peruvian government and people for "the
decisive action that was taken in defense of liberty, justice and
the rule of law in order to secure the release of the hostages and
resolve the long-standing explosive situation."
</P>
<P>
He also conveyed his deep condolences on the lives lost in the
operation to free the hostages.  
</P>
