<HEADLINE> NBA Players to Compete in Basketball Worlds: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 National Basketball
Association (NBA) players will join the United States squad for
next year's world championships in Greece, a NBA senior official
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
NBA deputy commissioner Russ Granik said at least 10 players of
the 12-strong team will be selected next autumn and "those will
all be NBA players."
</P>
<P>
"As we've done with preceding international events at a senior
level over the last several years, two spots will wait till the
spring and those could be players coming out of college or they
could also be NBA players," he told reporters covering Europe's
Final Four club championship.
</P>
<P>
Granik also confirmed that the new women's NBA, or WNBA, would
start on June 21 with eight teams, ending with the championship on
August 30. 
</P>
