<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Siemens Posts One Billion Marks Profit in First Half FY </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Siemens AG reported today
a net profit of 1.08 billion marks (635 million U.S. dollars) in
the first half of the 1996-97 fiscal year, thanks to strong growth
in the Americas and Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
In its interim report for the period ending on March 31, 1997,
the largest German electronics and engineering company said it had
seen new orders in the six months surging 11 percent, compared
with the same period of the previous fiscal year, to 53.9 billion
marks (31.7 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
This included foreign contracts worth 35.7 billion marks (21
billion dollars), up 20 percent over a year before, and domestic
orders of 18.2 billion marks (10.7 billion dollars), up only three
percent.
</P>
<P>
Siemens said it had harvested profits from the ongoing economic
boom in North and South America, where orders jumped 35 percent to
10.8 billion marks (6.4 billion dollars). In the Asia-Pacific
region, orders rose 28 percent to 7.3 billion marks (4.3 billion
dollars), boosted by a number of major contracts.
</P>
<P>
Siemens attributed the growth mainly to its telecommunications,
computer and automotive component operations.
</P>
<P>
Turnover in the year's first half increased six percent to 44.7
billion marks (26.3 billion dollars), with 28.2 billion marks
(16.6 billion dollars) abroad, up 11 percent, and 16.5 billion
marks (9.7 billion dollars) at home, down two percent.
</P>
<P>
Capital investments in the six-month period rose to 3.9 billion
marks (2.3 billion dollars), 14.7 percent higher than the 3.4
billion marks (2 billion dollars) in the same period of the
1995-96 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The company's payroll stood at 379,000 worldwide, the same
level as at the end of last fiscal year on October 1996, as a
staff reduction of 3,000 in Germany was offset by another 3,000
employees joining the company's international workforce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
