<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Gain on Positive Inflation Data </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares gained 1
percent, or nearly 25 points today on benign local inflation data,
strong futures trading and a surging Wall Street market.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries closed 24.7 points firmer at 2472.3.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials index rose 36.2 points to 3891.3 while the
All Resources index gained 16.4 points to 1377.8.
</P>
<P>
Nevitts Director Keiran Barrett said bank stocks performed
well, along with blue chips, fueled by Wall Street's gains and the
March inflation data out this morning.
</P>
<P>
The inflation data were within market expectations, with a 0.2-
percent rise in the annual inflation rate to 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The figure out today and the wages decision yesterday is
encouraging for an interest rate cut and that's clearly good for
any industrial stock, particularly banks," Julian Gregory from
Scott Foster said.
</P>
<P>
The bank index closed 41.8 points stronger at 4296.9 with
National Australia Bank up 17.4 cents.
</P>
<P>
But the gold index defied the positive trend, losing 13.3
points to 1586.5.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 389.66 million shares valued at
804.02 million Australian dollars ( 500.9 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
