<HEADLINE> Japan to Host Volleyball Worlds in 15 Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese Volleyball Association
has selected fifteen Japanese cities for the men's and women's
world volleyball championships in November next year.
</P>
<P>
The association said on Wednesday that 50 women's teams and 60
men's teams, including defending champions Cuba and Italy, have
entered the qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time in 24 years that the men's and
women's championships are held in the same country since 1974 in
Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen women's teams will be divided into four groups for the
preliminary round in Tokyo, Tokushima, Matsumoto and Kagoshima
starting from November 3.
</P>
<P>
The semi-finals will be played in Nagoya and Fukuoka, and the
finals slated for November 11 and 12 at Osaka.
</P>
<P>
The men's preliminaries will start on November 13 with 24 teams
playing in six groups. The top two from each group and the best
four third-placers will advance to the semi-final round in
Hiroshima, Chiba, Osaka and Hamamatsu.
</P>
<P>
The final round will be played in Tokyo on November 28 and 29.
</P>
</TEXT>
