<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Moves Ahead in Attempt to Secure Cyber- </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Singapore has taken another
step towards reality in its attempt to secure cyber-shopping, as
it launched here today a pilot project called Commerce Payment.
</P>
<P>
This project is a joint effort by the country's Network for
Electronic Transfer (NETS), Hewlett-Packard, Verifone, major banks
and credit card companies.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, cyber-shoppers will be issued digital
certificates by credit card companies that can be used at approved
websites. And retailers will be able to recognize genuine shoppers
through the certificates.
</P>
<P>
A senior executive officer of the NETS said that shoppers do
not have to pay a service charge for the service, which is only
open to credit card holders.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, plans are now in the pipeline to make it
available to other cash cards holders.
</P>
<P>
Some 4,000 shoppers and 75 retailers will take part in the
project till the end of this year, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
