<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Russian Duma Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today that efforts by China and Russia's top legislatures
have contributed to the smooth development of the two countries'
relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks this afternoon while meeting Gennady
Seleznev, Speaker of the State Duma, the lower house of Russian
parliament, and leaders of major parties in the Duma.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev extended warm welcome to Jiang's visit, saying that
the Duma is glad that top leaders of both countries have a wide
range of consensus on major international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary speaker said that both China and Russia
regard the world's multipolarization as necessary and he is
optimistic about the prospect of the Sino-Russian relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he had a fruitful talk with President Boris
Yeltsin this morning and that both considered it a proper choice
for the two countries to establish and develop a strategic
partnership of equality and mutual confidence oriented toward the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
"The choice has been made in light of past experiences of the
two sides and conforms with the requirements of the development of
the Post-Cold War international situation," Jiang said, adding
that such a choice is bound to win support from various circles in
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China expects to keep good-neighborly ties with
Russia and promote mutually-beneficial cooperation for mutual
development and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Duma speaker and many Duma members have been to
China before, Jiang said that they have made contributions to the
development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"We attach great importance to and support exchanges and
cooperation between the parliaments of the two sides, which are
conducive to enhancing mutual understanding and trust between the
two peoples and friendly cooperation between the two countries,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang invited Seleznev to visit China at his convenience and
hoped leaders of Russian parties to make travels to China. He
expressed his hope that all Duma members will be good friends of
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev agreed with Jiang, saying that the relations between
the two parliaments are being strengthened, with exchanges being
expanded.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev said that in order to promote the ties between the two
parliaments, a Russia-China Friendship Committee has been set up
within the Duma.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang conveyed to Seleznev greetings from
Qiao Shi, Chairman of the Standing Committee of China's National
People's Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
