<HEADLINE> Iran to Import 5 Million Tonnes of Wheat This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Iran will import 5 million
tonnes of wheat this year to meet the growing needs at home,
Persian daily Salam reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Iran's total wheat consumption has
been estimated at 10 million tons for this year, of which half
would be procured from domestic sources.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Karimi-Nouri, head of the Iran's Grain Organization,
said that Iran imported the same amount of wheat from other
countries and purchased 4.4 million tonnes from local farmers
last year.
</P>
<P>
Wheat is the main food item in the country, which is followed
by rice.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government said its population stands at less than
60 million at present. However, the U.N. population specialists
estimated its population at predicted 65 million at present.
</P>
</TEXT>
