<HEADLINE> Over 3,000 Smuggling Cases Busted in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam cracked 3,022 smuggling
cases in the first quarter of 1997, with the market value of the
confiscated goods totaling at some 5.5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to official reports here today, authorities seized
210 ancient relics, 6,636 kilograms of marijuana, 8.9 kilograms of
narcotics, 0.7 of kilograms heroin, and hundreds of books and
cultural products containing "anti-revolutionary," violent and
pornographic content.
</P>
<P>
These only accounted for "a small proportion" of the smuggling
cases nationwide. The cases were mostly found on sea routes and
along the northern and southwestern border, said customs sources.
