<HEADLINE> Hong Kong To Issue Commemorative Cover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) will issue a philatelic numismatic cover (PNC) to
commemorate the opening of the Lantau Fixed Crossing, one of Hong
Kong's 10 Airport Core Program projects.
</P>
<P>
The 5.5-km Lantau link, which runs between Tsing Yi Island and
Lantau Island, is composed of two bridges across the sea and a
viaduct on land. One part of the crossing is Tsing Ma Bridge,
which spans 1,377 meters and will be the world's longest
suspension bridge.
</P>
<P>
On the first-day cover, there is a commemorative stamp with the
design of the Lantau link; while inside is a 10-HK-dollar mint
coin featuring a suspension bridge. The design symbolizes the
smooth transition of Hong Kong in 1997.
</P>
<P>
A total of 50,000 sets will be issued worldwide, with 30,000
sets available in Hong Kong, according to a HKMA spokesman, who
said the PNC, the first ever issued in Hong Kong, would be of
great commemorative value.
</P>
<P>
The sale of the PNC, 188 HK dollars (24 US dollars) for each
set, will start on May 22, 1997, the day the Lantau Link is
scheduled to be opened to traffic.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
