<HEADLINE> Regional Derivative Products Listed on HK Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Stock Exchange
today launched two call warrants on regional index, the first time
regional derivative products are being traded on the local market.
</P>
<P>
The listing of the new products will provide more hedging and
investment vehicles for both domestic and overseas investors, said
Alec Tsui, chief executive of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong government has decided to remit stamp duty on
trading of regional derivative warrants and convertible bonds, a
move designed to encourage the development of more new products so
as to enhance Hong Kong's status as a regional and global
financial center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
