<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Trade Officials Visit Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong government
delegation started a two-day visit today to Guangdong Province in
southern China.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Director-General of Trade Alan Lai, will
meet with Guangdong officials, who oversee foreign economic
relations, trade and customs, to exchange views with them on
matters of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
Lai expressed the hope that the visit will further enhance the
trade relations and economic cooperation between the two places.
 
