<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Russia Set Up Friendship Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and Russian President Boris Yeltsin today announced the
official establishment of the Sino-Russian Friendship Committee
for Peace and Development.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders told reporters after signing a joint statement
in the Kremlin this morning that the committee is aimed at
promoting mutual understanding and friendship between the two
peoples to ensure a long-term, good-neighborly relationship of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The committee will consolidate and expand the social basis of
the strategic partnership of equality and mutual confidence
oriented toward the 21st century between China and Russia,
according to the two leaders.
</P>
<P>
The committee, consisting of 30 to 35 members from each of the
two countries, will focus on coordinating and promoting
non-governmental exchanges between the two countries, organizing
various kinds of non-governmental activities and putting forth
suggestions and proposals on the development of the Sino-Russian
relations.
</P>
<P>
The committee will be co-chaired by Huang Yicheng, vice
chairman of the Financial and Economic Committee under the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress, and
Arkady Bolsky, president of the Russian Union of Industrialists
and Entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
The first plenary session of the committee will be held in
Beijing in the second half of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
