<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Adds One More Restricted License Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) today granted a restricted banking license to
Citibank International, a subsidiary of one of the top five banks
in the world -- Citibank.
</P>
<P>
Headquartered in Miami, the United States, Citibank
International is engaged in such business as providing foreign
trade finance to American residents and accepting deposits from
non-US residents. It has opened branches in Honolulu, Houston, Los
Angeles and San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
Its new branch in Hong Kong will take over the existing credit
card business of Citibank here.
</P>
<P>
The grant has made Citibank International the 63th restricted
license bank in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
