<HEADLINE> ESCAP Begins 53rd Commission Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The 53rd commission session of
the U.N. Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific
(ESCAP) began here today, with Adrianus Mooy, ESCAP executive
secretary, calling on ESCAP to adapt itself to changing
conditions.
</P>
<P>
In his opening statement to the senior officials' segment of
the session, Mooy urged ESCAP members to provide guidance and
vision to ESCAP on its role in further accelerating economic and
social progress in the region.
</P>
<P>
The session will deliberate on this theme: "Asia and the
Pacific into the 21st century: opportunities and challenges for
the ESCAP region."
</P>
<P>
The session is divided into two tiers: that of senior officials
(from April 23 to 26) and that of ministers or vice ministers
(from April 28 to 30).
</P>
<P>
The participants will review the conference structure of the
commission, emerging issues and developments at the regional level
in regional economic cooperation; the environment and sustainable
development; poverty alleviation through economic growth and
social development; transport and communications; statistics; and
least-developed, land-locked and island developing countries.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday senior officials will discuss poverty alleviation
through economic growth and social development, transport and
communications, and statistics.
</P>
<P>
They will have informal consultations on Friday and Saturday
and consider draft reports for the ministerial segment to adopt.
</P>
</TEXT>
