<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More People Travel to Macao in Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The number of tourists traveling in
groups to Macao increased 17.9 percent in the first two months
this year, compared with the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department today show that Chinese mainland, Japan and Taiwan have
become the leading tourist market for Macao, accounting for 71.8
percent of all tourist groups.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of Macao residents traveling in groups
abroad reached 9,609 in February alone, up 12.9 percent. Most of
them were destined for Chinese mainland, Thailand, Singapore and
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that 430,284 passengers checked in Macao
hotels in the first two months, up 4.6 percent. The average hotel
room occupancy rate rose 2.6 percent to 58.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Earlier statistics show that the number of visitor arrivals to
Macao dropped 1.6 percent in January and February. A total of
1,288,466 arrivals were recorded.
</P>
<P>
More than 8.15 million visitors arrived in Macao in 1996, and
the government estimated that this year's figure would reach nine
million.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
