<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Expand Social Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Expanding the coverage of social
insurance has become an urgent task for the Vietnamese government,
press reports said here today.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of War Invalids and Social
Affairs told the English-language daily, Vietnam News, that the
expansion of a social insurance system was important for the
welfare of the Vietnamese workers.
</P>
<P>
He said it was necessary to expand insurance service to all
workers in every economic sector.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam now has about 37 million workers, but only six million
or 15 percent of the total, have bought compulsory insurance.
</P>
<P>
According to government regulations, insurance fund comes from
contributions equivalent to 20 percent of each worker's salary.
</P>
<P>
But, only five percent is deducted directly from a worker's
wage while 15 percent comes from his employer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
