<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKCEC Extension to Be Completed in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center (HKCEC) Extension, the venue of the historic
handover ceremony on midnight June 30, is scheduled for completion
on June 2.
</P>
<P>
A charity dinner for 2,700 people will be held on June 14 to
celebrate the completion of the 4.8-billion-HK-dollar (615 million
 U.S. dollars) complex, Chairman of the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC) Victor Fung told a press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
The charity dinner, jointly organized by the TDC, the Community
Chest of Hong Kong and the HKCEC, will be the first major event to
take place in the Extension and also a rehearsal of a grand
banquet catering to some 4,000 dignitaries from all over the world
on the handover night.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by the image of a seabird soaring into the sky, the
low-rise Extension will be a new landmark on the Hong Kong
Island's harbor front, symbolizing Hong Kong's importance as a
regional business hub, Fung said.
</P>
<P>
It will be characterized by a sculptural curved roof, which,
ranked among the largest curved roof structures in the world, will
be finished with 40,000 square meters of aluminum cladding.
</P>
<P>
"This is a building all of us should be proud of," Fung
declared.
</P>
<P>
"The extension project well reflects Hong Kong's quest for
excellence. Experts from over 10 countries and regions
collaborated and materials from over 30 countries were sourced to
ensure that the building is designed and constructed to keep
abreast of the highest international standard," he continued.
</P>
<P>
The expanded HKCEC is more than double the size of the existing
center. It will be the second largest exhibition and convention
facility in Asia, with space totaling 63,580 square meters.
</P>
<P>
"The expanded HKCEC will become the city's super showcase and
Hong Kong will be able to measure the economic benefit in billions
of dollars each year across all industries and services sectors,"
Fung said.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that trade flows generated directly from
transactions within the expanded HKCEC could be as high as 68.6
billion HK dollars (8.8 billion U.S. dollars) a year, or 2.3
percent of Hong Kong's total trade value of 2.933 trillion HK
dollars (376 billion U.S. dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The extension project was entrusted to the TDC by the Hong Kong
government in March 1994, before reclamation and construction
began in June that year.
</P>
<P>
In September 1996, it was announced that China and Britain had
agreed to hold the handover ceremony in the Extension, to be
specific, in the Grand Foyer on Level 5, which catches a
180-degree panoramic harbor view through a huge glass facade.
</P>
<P>
This year's World Bank and International Monetary Fund annual
meeting will also take place in the Extension in September.
</P>
</TEXT>
