<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Village Becomes No. One Foreign Exchange Earner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Dongguan village in Yuzhou
city, in central China's Henan province has earned 12 million US
dollars from exports, making it first among all the province's
villages.
</P>
<P>
The village head cited Dongguan as a typical traditional
farming village in the past, but said that in 1993 it began
developing policies that would help it attract better personnel.
</P>
<P>
The village of 4,000 people now has more than 600 enterprises
of different kinds involved in machine making, building
maaterials, and other fields. Its products have been exported to
the United States, Singapore, the Republic of Korea (ROK), Japan,
Hong Kong, and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Dongguan set up joint ventures with the US, the ROK,
and Taiwan to bring in more advanced equipment and technology.
</P>
</TEXT>
