<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Injured After Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- World women's tennis number one
player Martina Hingis has injured her knee after falling from a
horse and will be out of the WTA Tour for three weeks.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Swiss player was riding in the canton of St
Gall in eastern Switzerland where she lives with her mother when
the accident happened.
</P>
<P>
Czeck-born Hingis hoisted herself up after the fall with a
laugh, but the next morning found she could not stretch her left
leg.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will miss tournaments in Hamburg, Rome, and Berlin
scheduled during the next three weeks.
</P>
<P>
The forced rest will not change Hingis' number one ranking, she
is 771 points ahead of number two Steffi Graf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
