<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Gives Speech at Russian Duma (Part IV) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Russia is a great country. With its vast landmass spanning
Europe and Asia, splendid history and culture, rich natural
resources and industrious and talented people, Russia has a great
potential for development. The Russian people have made
significant contributions to world civilization and human progress
and performed indelible historical services for the victory of the
world anti-fascist war. This great nation is entitled to a proper
place and dignity in the world. As your friendly neighbor, we
sincerely wish you social stability, economic rejuvenation and
your people well-being.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government attaches great importance to developing
friendly and good-neighborly relations with Russia and considers
it as an important aspect of its foreign relations. At present,
the two countries are dedicated to establishing and developing a
strategic partnership of equality and trust geared towards the
21st century. As a new type of state-to-state relationship, this
partnership is based on the following purposes: To deepen
bilateral cooperation, maintain long-term friendship and
good-neighborliness and promote common development and prosperity
to serve the well-being of the two peoples, to intensify bilateral
consultation and coordination in international affairs, uphold
sovereignty, independence and national dignity of the two
countries and safeguard their respective due status and legitimate
rights and interests in the international arena, to bring about a
relaxed and stable international situation through cooperation and
joint effort and push forward the trend of global
multipolarization and the establishment of a just and equitable
new international order. This new relationship between China and
Russian is nothing more than a relationship of friendship and
cooperation. It is not an alliance. Rather than being directed
against any third country or posing a threat to any one, this
relationship serves peace and security in the region and the world
at large and is completely consistent with the trends of the times
and the needs of the shifting international relations.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to efforts of both sides, this strategic partnership is
moving ahead on all fronts. Regular contacts and exchanges
between the leaders of the two countries have become
institutionalized and a hot line between the two governments is
soon to come into operation. Exchanges and contacts between the
two parliaments are also strengthened steadily. Both China and
Russia are rich in natural resources and possess vast markets.
Highly complementary economically, the two countries have seen
their economic relations expanding and their cooperation in the
field of science and technology deepening with each passing day.
The goals set by the two sides for a growing bilateral trade by
the end of the century will surely become reality. There are more
than 4,000 kilometers of common border between the two countries,
most of which has been affirmed in the form of legal
instrument. The remaining border issues left over from history are
being resolved gradually, which will lay a solid foundation for
enhanced trust and closer friendship and good-neighborliness
between the two countries. Both being major powers of influence
and permanent members of the U.N. Security Council, China and
Russia shoulder an important responsibility for safeguarding world
peace and stability. The two sides have similar or identical views
on a host of major international issues and are stepping up
coordination and cooperation in their handling of global and
regional affairs. The Sino-Russian Committee on Friendship, Peace
and Development, which has just been inaugurated, will surely play
an important role in broadening the people-to-people exchanges and
enhancing their mutual understanding and trust between the two
peoples.
</P>
<P>
To sum up, the strategic cooperation between China and Russia
enjoys a solid basis, a broad scope, vast potentials and bright
prospects. Our two peoples are bound forever to be good neighbors,
good partners and good friends. And the tree of friendship between
the two peoples will be evergreen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
