<HEADLINE> Jinqiao Development Zone, An Economic Drive in Shanghai, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Jinqiao Development Zone,
the largest export-oriented processing zone in the Pudong New Area
in Shanghai, is expected to have 100 billion yuan in annual
industrial output value by the turn of the century, a big leap
from 15 billion yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The zone attracted 5.5 billion US dollars of investment and
introduced 302 projects, 141 of which have gone into
operation. Its industrial output value has totalled 35 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The zone has 73 industrial projects with investment beyond 10
million US dollars each, and 20 with investment more than 30
million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
As many as 48 multinational companies have poured capital into
the zone, which has built up various hi-tech industries such as:
microelectronics, telecom, automobiles and parts, integration of
optics, machinery, and electronics, and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
At a cost exceeding 1.675 billion US dollars, the zone added 35
projects last year, 25 of which are involved in the fields of
integrated circuits, new alloys, genetic engineering, electronic
components for camera, CFC-free refrigerators, precision moulds,
precision machine tools, and state-of-the-art household
appliances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
