<HEADLINE> U.S. to Host Davis Cup Semis on Hardcourt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The United States will boost
their winning chance by hosting its Davis Cup tennis tournament
semifinal against Australia on hardcourt, Tennis Australia (TA)
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tie in September will be played in either Raleigh, North
Carolina, or Washington D.C. from September 19-21, the Australian
tennis body said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The decision could mean that world number one Pete Sampras of
the United States, an expert on hardcourt surface, would probably
take part in the competition, TA said.
</P>
<P>
Australia sailed into the last four by beating Czech Republic
5-0 earlier this month, while the Americans defeated the
Netherlands 4-1.
</P>
<P>
The winner will meet either Sweden or Italy in the Davis Cup
final in late November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
