<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed in
thin trading on the Singapore market with the benchmark Straits
Time Industrials Index declining by 12.76 points to finish at
2034.8 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 130.88 million units, valued
at 377.89 million Singapore dollars (about 262.42 million U.S.
dollars). Advances led declines by 158 to 145 while 317 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Summit was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 11.52 million units. It was followed by Ber Ind. which
had 10.54 million shares traded. The Singapore Telecom was next
with 6.9 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
C Properties led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1.5
Singapore dollars to close at 19 Singapore dollars. Ber Leis
gained 38 cents to end at 3.8 Singapore dollars, while Ber Lei
warrant 99 finished 36 cents higher at 2.25 Singapore dollars. The
Singapore Airlines Foreign picked up 30 cents to reach 12.4
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local computer sound cards maker Creative 50
declined by 1 Singapore dollar to end at 19.6 Singapore dollars.
Malaya Resources 97 fell by 86 cents to close at 3.5 dollars,
while car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) was 70 cents lower at
14.8 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
