<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets ROK Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress, met
here today with a delegation of the Junior Chamber of the Republic
of Korea (ROK) led by its national president Kang Shin-sung.
</P>
<P>
Wang expressed his high appreciation over the chamber's efforts
in promoting friendly contacts between the two countries and the
bilateral unofficial economic and trade co-operation.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that such co-operation will be further reinforced.
</P>
<P>
Kang said that his generation of both ROK and China are playing
a key role in the economic construction of their respective
countries and even the overall economic progress of Asia,
therefore, to improve their co-operation will be of profound
significance.
</P>
<P>
The Junior Chamber, an unofficial economic organization
composed by ROK enterpreneurs under the age of 40, has carried out
fruitful co-operation with the All-China Youth Federation since
1992 when they first forged links.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
