<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Attaches Great Importance to Sino-Russian Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
today that the Chinese Government attaches great importance to
developing friendly and good-neighborly relations with Russia and
considers them as an important aspect of its foreign relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the statement in an address delivered at Russia's
State Duma (lower house).
</P>
<P>
He said at present, the two countries are dedicated to
establishing and developing a strategic partnership of equality
and trust geared towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He added that as a new type of state-to-state relationship,
this partnership aims to deepen bilateral cooperation, maintain
long-term friendship and good-neighborliness and promote common
development and prosperity to serve the well-being of the two
peoples.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President said this partnership also aims to
intensify bilateral consultation and coordination in international
affairs, uphold sovereignty, independence and national dignity of
the two countries and safeguard their respective due status and
legitimate rights and interests in the international order.
</P>
<P>
He said: "This new relationship between China and Russia is
nothing more than a relationship of friendship and cooperation.
It is not an alliance."
</P>
<P>
"Rather than being directed against any third country or posing
a threat to any one, this relationship serves peace and security
in the region and the world at large and is completely consistent
with the trends of the times and the needs of the shifting
international relations," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that thanks to efforts of both sides, this strategic
partnership is moving ahead on all fronts. Regular contacts and
exchanges between the leaders of the two countries have become
institutionalized and a hot line between the two governments is
soon to come into operation.
</P>
<P>
He noted that exchanges and contacts between the two
parliaments are also strengthened steadily.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that both China and Russia are rich
in natural resources and possess vast markets, and their economies
are highly complementary to each other.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have seen their economic relations expanding
and their cooperation in the field of science and technology
deepening with each passing day, he said.
</P>
<P>
He asserted that the goals set by the two sides for a growing
bilateral trade by the end of the century will surely become
reality.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 4,000 kilometers of common borders between
the two countries, most of which have been affirmed in the form of
legal instrument, he said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say the remaining border issues left over from
history are being resolved gradually, which will lay a solid
foundation for enhanced trust and closer friendship and
good-neighborliness between the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said since both China and Russia are major powers of
influence and permanent members of the U.N. Security Council, they
should shoulder an important responsibility for safeguarding world
peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries have similar or identical views on a
host of major international issues and are stepping up
coordination and cooperation in their handling of global and
regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Russian Committee on Friendship, Peace and
Development, which has just been inaugurated, will surely play an
important role in broadening the people-to-people exchanges and
enhancing their mutual understanding and trust between the two
peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said, "The strategic cooperation between
China and Russia enjoys a solid basis, a broad scope, vast
potentials and bright prospects."
</P>
<P>
"Our two peoples are bound forever to be good neighbors, good
partners and good friends. And the tree of friendship between the
two peoples will be evergreen," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
