<HEADLINE> US Bearings Company Opens Office in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The leading international
manufacturer of highly engineered bearings and alloy steels, the
Timken Company from the U.S., has opened a representative office
in Beijing, to strengthen its business development in China.
</P>
<P>
The nearly 100-year-old company already has representative
offices in Hong Kong and Shanghai and has a joint venture in
Yantai, a port city in East China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The company's bearings are made for aircraft landings and cars.
</P>
<P>
Joseph F. Toot, Jr., president and chief executive officer of
the Timken Company, said at a press conference here today that
he's very pleased with the operations in China and that Timken has
been "fairly and well treated by all parties in China."
</P>
<P>
"We want to continue to grow in China," he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Yantai joint venture, which was set up a year
ago, plans to produce six million sets of bearings this year,
adding that the company will basically service the China market in
the first phase and will export later. 
</P>
