<HEADLINE> China to Continue With Its Open, Reform Policies, Jiang Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China will stick to its policies
of opening up and reform, Chinese President Jiang Zemin told the
Russian State Duma (lower house of parliament) today.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of reform and opening-up 19 years ago,
China has witnessed spectacular economic expansion, marked
improvement in people's living standards, increased ethnic harmony
and a dynamic and vigorous national life, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
All this has been achieved under the guidance of Deng
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, said Jiang, adding that the theory is the single
most precious asset of the Chinese Communist Party and the Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
Though Comrade Deng is no longer with us, China's current
domestic and foreign policies will not change, nor is there any
such possibility, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
These policies were formulated in accordance with China's
national interests and the will of its people. They suit to
China's national conditions, and have received the wholehearted
support of the Chinese people, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will carry forward Comrade Deng Xiaoping's behest, and,
holding high the great banner of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, advance steadily our cause of reform, opening-up
and modernization," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
In some 60 days, the Chinese Government will resume the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong. "This is a major step
towards the accomplishment of our grand cause of national
reunification," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"We will ensure Macao's smooth return and the final settlement
of the Taiwan question by continuing to follow the `one country,
two systems' policy, for this represents the common aspiration of
the entire Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
China cannot develop itself in isolation of the rest of the
world and the world also needs China for its own development. The
maintenance of long-term social stability and economic prosperity
in China is crucial both to the country itself and to the world at
large.
</P>
<P>
China will unswervingly keep to the road of development suited
to its national conditions while vigorously absorbing all the
achievements of human civilization. China stands ready to conduct
extensive international cooperation on the basis of world peace
and development, Jiang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
