is aimed to realize self-sufficiency in all crops and raise per
capita income to 4,500 dollars annually, said Youssef Wali,
Egyptian deputy premier and minister of agriculture and land
reclamation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before a week-long forum on investment and
agricultural development in the Egyptian governorates, Wali said
the government has been keen on amending the investment law with a
view to giving the governorates more access to investment in the
country.
</P>
