BEIRUT -- OPEC's Vienna-based National Development Fund has
provided Lebanon with a loan of seven million U.S. dollars, the
forth amount of 24 million dollars the Lebanon has received from
OPEC, the Daily Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper reported that the 17-year loan, carrying 3 percent
interest and 1 percent service charge, will be used to
reconstruct small schools in an attempt to improve technical
education. 
