<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Doctors Reduce Recurrence Rate of Cataract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai doctors have found a
way to keep patients from relapsing into cataract after the
operation.
</P>
<P>
Extracapsular cataract extraction is a safe and effective
method to treat cataracts, a common disease, which can result in
blindness. But many patients suffered from the capsular opacity
and other complications after the operation, which led to their
declining eye sights.
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of late Professor Lu Daoyan, founder of the
hospital's department of ophthalmology, doctors at Shanghai Xinhua
Hospital, led by Wang Litian and Chen Caigen, have found a new
method, which can raise the success rate of cultivating the
epithelial cells, one of the vital procedures in treating
cataracts.
</P>
<P>
The hospital has selected medicines, which proved effective in
reducing the recurrence rate of cataract after the operation, and
will soon produce the medicine on a larger scale.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970423.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ruggiero Confident About China's WTO Accession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- WTO director-general Renato
Ruggiero told a press conference here today that he is satisfied
with the result of his China trip and optimistic about China's
accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero said that the WTO is satisfied with the efforts and
response that China has made in its bid to join the WTO. He said
that as long as all parties show a sense of urgency and necessary
flexibility and concentrate on the process of negotiation, they
will finally achieve a balance of interest.
</P>
<P>
"We are and should be optimistic," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's development in recent years has been
closely linked with opening its economy to the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
He hopes that the next round of negotiation on China's
accession to the WTO in May will achieve more progress on the
issue and maintain the momentum of previous negotiations so as to
conclude the issue on an earliest possible date.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out the without the participation of China, the
fifth trade partner in the world and a nation accounting for
one-fifth of the world population, the WTO cannot achieve its
ambitious goal to set up a 21st century international system based
on universal rules. 
</P>
