<HEADLINE> North China Province's Telecom Developments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- There are now 14.56 telephones
for every 100 urban residents in north China's Shanxi Province, a
great change when compared with the 4.56 telephones of recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The change comes as a result of the province's having spent
more than 5.8 billion yuan over the past six years on fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
All prefectures and cities in the province have individual
telecom networks and have increased their telephone numbers to
seven digits. They have also built TV conference networks and are
covered by mobile telecome and paging services. The province now
has more than 91,010 mobile phone customers and 350,000 who use
pagers.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of the year, the province had a nearly 67
percent increase in business in the telecoms sector from the same
period of 1996, 31 percentage points more than the national
average.  
