<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increases Fixed Assets Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai put more than 21.4
billion yuan into fixed assets during the first quarter of this
year, a 21 percent increase over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 66 percent of the amount went to the local service
trade, an increase of 22 percent over the same period of 1996. The
other 7.2 billion yuan was used for developing local industry.
</P>
<P>
The three-month period also saw the city spending more than 4.8
billion yuan on urban infrastructure like its second subway, an
elevated highway over the east section of Yan'an Road, a highway
to Hangzhou, and a water diversion project on the Huangpu
River. This construction spending was a 93 percent increase over
1996.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the volume of investment in the Pudong
New Area surpassed 6.1 billion yuan, up 87 percent from the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai had more than 31.35 billion yuan for use in local
construction during the three-month period, up nearly 54.8 percent
from the same period of 1996. Of this amount, the volume of
overseas investment and domestic loans rose by 130 percent and 59
percent, respectively, from 1996.  
</P>
