<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Southern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.8
degrees on the open-ended Richter scale hit the southern Iranian
city of Firouzabad, about 800 kilometers south of Tehran Tuesday
night, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that a number of
houses have been damaged, but there has been no information on
whether there were any casualties.
</P>
<P>
The seismological center of Shiraz, affiliated to Geophysics
Institute of Tehran University, said that the epicenter of the
quake was located 150 kilometers Shiraz between Ghir-Karzin
district and Firouzabad.
</P>
<P>
Early March, 965 people were killed and 2,600 wounded in a
deadly earthquake which rocked Ardebil region in northeastern
Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
