<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Russia Committed to Bilateral Strategic Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia today expressed
their satisfaction over the strategic partnership between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement issued today, the two countries said their
strategic partnership, based on equality and trust and oriented
towards the 21st century, conforms to the global trend of
development and international relations in the post-Cold War world.
</P>
<P>
Such a parternship fully serves the fundamental interests of
the two peoples and conduces to peace and security in the
Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole, said the statement,
which was signed by Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Russian
President Boris Yeltsin today.
</P>
<P>
It constitutes an important practice towards the establishment
of a new international order for China and Russia, both permanent
members of the U.N. Security Council, to forge a partnership that
is characterized by good neighborliness and friendship, equality
and trust, mutually-beneficial cooperation and common development,
in strict compliance with the principles of international law and
formulation of a new type of long-term state-to-state relationship
not directed against any other country, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides expressed readiness to vigorously employ and
strengthen the existing system of summit meetings and high-level
contacts whereby their heads of state and government and foreign
ministers meet regularly to exchange views on bilateral relations
and major internation issues.
</P>
<P>
With a sense of historical responsibility for world peace,
development and the future of mankind, the two sides pledged their
closer coordination and cooperation in international affairs, and
their commitment to harmonious coexistence and cooperation on an
equal footing with all other countries with a view to contributing
their due share to the lasting peace in the world and the common
progress of mankind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
