<HEADLINE> Trade Zone Close to Taiwan Expanding Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Weitou, in Quanzhou City, in east
China's Fujian Province, is speeding up the construction of basic
facilities, to promote its trade with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Weitou is only five nautical miles away from Taiwan's island of
Jinmen. Last year, the zone's trade with Taiwan reached more than
ten million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Weitou is building a 10,000-tonnage berth, and expanding a
running water plant with a daily supply capacity of 10,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
A 110,000-volt power substation will be built to complement the
zone's 35,000-volt substation. Weitou's 10,000 program-controled
telephone lines are convenient for links with Taiwan, sources say.
</P>
<P>
The zone invested 12 million yuan to build 8,000 square meters
of commercial stands and other service facilities, which will be
rented to local and Taiwanese business people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
