<DOCNO> XIE19970423.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN to Render 120 Million Dollars to Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. will render 120 Million
dollars to Turkey in a bid to develop eastern and southeastern
Anatolia, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Daily News quoted U.N. Representative
to Turkey Paul van Hanswick de Jonge as saying that the U.N.
would not only give the 120 million dollars to Turkey, but
also provide technical support as well.
</P>
<P>
"The U.N. has been supporting projects established in western
Turkey for 40 years, but from now on, most of new U.N. funds will
be spent to develop eastern and southeastern Anatolia," De Jonge
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Turkish education sector was in need of
support and there was a huge difference between the ratios of
the educated people from the east and west.
</P>
<P>
Education possibilities and the ratio of the educated people
are very low in the east compared to the west, said the
U.N. representative.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Supporting the education sector will promote the
development process in a positive way."
</P>
<P>
On the Turkish economy, De Jonge said that "Turkey has a
special place among the developing countries and has great
economic potential." 
</P>
</TEXT>
