<DOCNO> XIE19970423.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Russia Calls for Strengthening of U.N. Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia said in a joint
statement today that the role of the United Nations (U.N.) and its
Security Council should be strengthened and that the U.N. efforts
in maintaining world peace and security merit a positive appraisal.
</P>
<P>
As the most representative and authoritative organization
composed of sovereign states, the U.N. has a world capacity that
no other international organization can possibly replace, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia are convinced that the U.N. ought to play an
important role in the establishment and maintenance of a new
international order.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. peacekeeping efforts should focus on the prevention of
the occurrence and spread of conflicts. Peacekeeping operations
can be undertaken only by the decision of the U.N. Security
Council and the approval of the countries concerned, and in strict
compliance with the Security Council mandate and its supervision,
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
When deciding to impose sanctions in accordance with relevant
provisions of the U.N. Charter, the Security Council should see to
it that the losses caused by the measure as well as the losses it
brings to third countries and adjacent areas be reduced to the
minimum and that the sanctions be lessened or removed in due
course in light of the implementation of the Security Council
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia agreed to step up their close cooperation with
the U.N. and its specialized agencies towards greater efficiency
of the organization.
</P>
<P>
They said they stand ready to keep up regular consultations on
subjects relating to the work of the U.N. and to coordinate their
respective actions in this regard in light of circumstances.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970423.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
