<HEADLINE> China Sets up Committee to Promote Regional Security Co-operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China established a committee of
the Council for Security Co-operation in Asia Pacific (CSCAP) here
today to promote peace and development of the region.
</P>
<P>
Li Luye, the first President of the China Committee, and some
40 officials and experts from government departments and academic
institutes took part in the inauguration meeting today. Assistant
Foreign Minister Chen Jian presided over the meeting and delivered
the key-note speech.
</P>
<P>
