<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim said on
Tuesday there is need for the OAU to streamline its organs and
structures to make it more effective.
</P>
<P>
He said after meeting with Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
it was important for the OAU to streamline its organs and
structures to make it more effective so that Africans identified
and recognized OAU as a continental institution.
</P>
<P>
On his chances for re-election, Salim said he was looking
forward to another term of office when the current term expires
next month.
</P>
<P>
He added his mission to Zimbabwe was to liaise with the
Zimbabwean government on the preparations and agenda for the 33rd
ordinary session of the OAU assembly of heads of state and
government from May 26 to June 4.
</P>
<P>
