<HEADLINE> Chinese Light Aircraft Get State Approval </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Two types of light aircrafts
developed by Beijing Aviation and Aerospace University,
recently got approval from the Civil Aviation Administration of
China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
The Bee-3c and Bee-11 are the latest members of the
unicersity's Bee series of aircraft, developed by a group led by
Prof. Hu Jizhong, a prominent plane designer.
</P>
<P>
The Bee-3c has a speed of 90 kph and a payload of 80 kg. It can
be used for aerial photography and can land on rough terrain.
</P>
<P>
The Bee-11 has light wings and a speed of 134 kph and payload
of 120 kg.
</P>
<P>
There are about 200 light aircraft being used in various parts
of China, more than 50 percent of which were developed by the
university. 
