<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Export Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The export sector of China's
largest metropolis has been showing steady progress, according to
Zhou Hongli, Deputy Director of the city's Foreign Economic and
Trade Commission, who is attending the 18th Guangzhou Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said that last year, Shanghai's exports amounted to 13.24
billion US dollars, up 14.3 percent, and in the first three months
of this year, its exports were worth 3.3 billion US dollars, up
10.3 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Pudong New Area now accounts for a fifth of the city's
total exports, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven days of the Guangzhou fair, Shanghai did 334
million US dollars worth of export business, a 6.3 percent
increase over last fair's fair, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai got contracts at the fair for 51 Santana cars, he
said, the first time for Shanghai to sell its cars for export at
the Guangzhou Trade Fair. 
