<HEADLINE> Iran Starts Second Stage of War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Iran today started the second
stage of the amphibious maneuvers code-named "Path to Jerusalem"
with the participation of 300 military vessels of various types in
the Persian Gulf waters.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that Ali Khamenei,
Iran's Supreme Leader and Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces,
watched the war games carried out by the Islamic Revolutionary
Guards Corps (IRGC).
</P>
<P>
The report said that the first stage of the war games was
launched Tuesday evening in the presence of Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
IRGC Commander Mohsen Rezai and Commanders of Ground, Air,
Naval and Basij (volunteer) forces of the corps briefed Khamenei
on the features of the three-day war games.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Khamenei also inspected the "Qadr"
(value) missile launching vessel where he was briefed on the
vessel's military features and defense capabilities.
</P>
<P>
A total of 200,000 marines and ground force personnel of the
IRGC Basij forces are participating in the maneuvers covering
2,000 kilometers of the western and southern borders of Iran.
</P>
<P>
The three-phase maneuvers were intended to test and
demonstrate the combat readiness of the Iranian forces on land,
in air and sea. However, Iran claimed that the maneuvers were
planned as defensive and deterrent operations.
</P>
<P>
During the maneuvers, scores of weapons of various kinds and
boats as well as naval equipment will be tested for their performance.
</P>
