<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Gezhouba Dam Produces Economic Benefits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Gezhouba Dam on the middle
reaches of Yangtze River has generated 187.8 billion kw/hours of
electricity in the last 15 years and 15 billion yuan worth of
social and economic benefits for central and east China.
</P>
<P>
The dam, which is located in Yichang City in central China's
Hubei Province, has a designed generating capacity of 2.7 million
kw and an annual output of 14.09 billion kw/hours of electricity.
</P>
<P>
It is not far from the construction site of the giant Three
Gorges Dam project.
</P>
<P>
Water conservation experts say that, based on data collected at
the river over a 110-year period that Gezhouba can generate 16.7
billion kw/hours of electricity at most in a good year and could
produce 13.8 billion kw/hours of power in a bad year.
</P>
<P>
It has proved itself to be energy efficient and has helped
connect the central and east China power grid to the national
power grid. Experts say that it provided experience for the Three
Gorges water control dam in terms of construction, operation, and
management.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
