<HEADLINE> Malaysia Plays Role in Sri Lanka's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia which has over 51.72
million U.S. dollars investment in Sri Lanka, will play an
important role in the development of the country's economy,
Malaysian High Commission sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that potential for Malaysian investment in Sri
Lanka was enormous. There are 26 Malaysian projects in Sri Lanka.
Once the country's ethnic problem was solved, there would be a
flood of investment from Malaysia and elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
They said that there was a lot of scope for trade expansion
between the two countries. Malaysia is emerging as one of the
largest trading nations in the world. Today it was the world's
19th largest exporter and 17th largest importer.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between the two countries was gradually growing
in recent years. Sri Lanka imported goods worth 110.5 million U.S.
dollars and exported to Malaysia goods worth around 19.3 million
dollars in 1996, the sources added.  
