<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's gross domestic product
is expected to increase by more than 3 percent this year, the
Central Bank of Portugal said today.
</P>
<P>
The economic growth rate in 1997 is expected to be between 3
percent and 3.75 percent, a bank report said. Portugal's GDP in
1996 rose by 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
