<HEADLINE> Myanmar Declares Eradication of Narcotics in Mongla </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has declared that
narcotics have been completely eradicated in Mongla region, east
of Kengtung in the Shan state bordering China.
</P>
<P>
Quoting Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the
Myanmar State Law and Order Restoration Council, the official
paper The New Light of Myanmar today said there is no longer
cultivation of narcotic plants and drug trafficking in the region.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting with members of local authorities in
Kengtung Tuesday, Khin Nyunt disclosed that development of the
region is to be underway with preparatory measures to be taken for
the purpose.
</P>
<P>
With the cooperation of the Myanmar government, the Shan people
have been implementing a six-year plan for eradication of poppy
cultivation and opium production in Kengtung east region since
1991 after the local armed group returned to the legal fold in
1989.
</P>
<P>
Mongla is one of the three areas covered by the operation plan,
the other two being Nampan and Silu.  
</P>
</TEXT>
