<HEADLINE> Over 18,000 Private Enterprises Operate in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Private business enterprises,
registered with the Myanmar Ministry for Operation, totaled 18,769
by the end of January this year, according to the latest figures
published by the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises, which are running in various forms, include
8,521 Myanmar companies, 7,143 exporters and importers, 1,940
business representatives, 1,162 partnership firms and 3 chambers
of commerce.
</P>
<P>
Active and increased participation of private sector especially
in the areas of trade and investment has played a leading role in
Myanmar since it moved towards market-oriented economy in late
1988.
</P>
<P>
According to the official statistics, the contribution of
private sector to the GDP and export were 76.4 percent and 50.2
percent respectively.  
</P>
