<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Moves to Improve Tourism Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China's capital city is
tightening up tourism services and coming down hard on con artists
and ripoff merchants in a bid to bolster a successful Visit
China '97, according to a report in today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Beijing Municipal Tourism Administration will continue efforts
to improve the capital's tourist market after a fruitful campaign
of the same kind carried out last year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Any tourist center staff member, tour guide or bus driver who
asks for a commission will be charged with bribery. And travel
agencies without authorized business licenses will be banned, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The actions also include punishing travel agencies with
domestic business licenses who receive overseas tourists or
organize tours abroad without authorization.
</P>
<P>
"Other practices like dodging taxes, employing tour guides
without authorized professional certificates or overcharging
visitors will be scrutinized", the report said.
</P>
<P>
The tourist market watchdogs will punish vendors, snack bar
owners and bus drivers at major scenic spots who rip off tourists,
especially foreigners, it said.
</P>
<P>
The authorities also plan to carry out inspections of fake and
low-quality tourism commodities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
