<HEADLINE> Xi'an Sets Up New Fund to Help Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- China's northwest city of Xi'an
is planning to establish a new fund to help the redundant find new
jobs.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi Province, is to provide a fund worth
60 million yuan (7.23 million US dollars). The money will be used
to establish industries to provide work for the jobless, according
to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Xi'an used to have many military factories and large and
middle-sized state-owned enterprises, but it has suffered from the
market reforms since the early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Some 90,000 workers lost their jobs by the end of 1996, but
more than 60,000 have been re-employed, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The local government is also encouraging other ventures in the
city to help the jobless, the paper added. 
</P>
