<HEADLINE> Andean Countries to Boost Ties with Regional Blocs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUCRE, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The four countries of the South
American bloc, the Andean Group, is to speed up integration with
other regional economic blocs around the world.
</P>
<P>
At the start of a presidential summit of the group, now made
up of Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador and Venezuela after Peru quit
earlier this month, the members also vowed to promote cooperation
with the South American Common Market (Mercosur), the largest
regional trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
The second draft of the Sucre Act, to be signed tomorrow, asked
the Andean council of foreign ministers and the group's committee
to conclude negotiations with Mercosur on a bilateral trade
agreement by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, comprising Brazil, Argentina, Paraguay, Uruguay
accounts for 45 percent of the Latin American population and more
than a third of its foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The pact also pledged to strengthen relations with the European
Union and to institutionalize dialogue with China. 
</P>
