<HEADLINE> Ramos Urged to Anoint Successor Before Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the ruling Lakas-NUCD
party preferred that President Fidel Ramos anoints his successor
before the party holds its national convention.
</P>
<P>
Lakas leaders said an early anointment will ensure the ruling
party to rally behind a single candidate, the Manila Chronicle
reported today. However, the paper did not explain when the
national convention will be held.
</P>
<P>
According to Presidential Legal Adviser Narciso Nario, the
national directorate is giving Ramos a mandate to anoint the
Lakas-NUCD bet before the convention.
</P>
<P>
Selecting the successor as early as possible will be better as
it will affirm the confidence of the entire membership of the
party to the leadership of the anointed, Nario said.
</P>
<P>
Nario admitted that the party's national convention is
"divisive and offensive" if there will be many choices among its
members.
</P>
<P>
House Speaker Jose de Venecia and Defense Secretary Renato de
Villa are considered strong rivals for the party's nomination. To
get the endorsement of the president, De Villa hinted he would
join the ruling party.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that President Ramos' endorsement is worth a
minimum of four million votes, a guarantee of success for the
anointed one in the 1998 presidential elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
