<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake registering 5.5 on
the Richter scale Tuesday rocked northern areas of Bengkulu in
southwestern Sumatra, Indonesia, a monitoring official said here.
</P>
<P>
Meteorology and geophysics official Subagyo said last night
that the quake hit at 12:55 p.m. with the epicenter in a remote
area 100 kilometers north of the city of Bengkulu.
</P>
<P>
Subagyo said he had not received any report of injuries or
damage. The jolts were felt in Bengkulu and neighboring towns, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The area around the epicenter is mountainous and "sparsely
populated as far as I know," he said.  
</P>
