<HEADLINE> Latin American Economic News Briefs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The projected growth of the gross domestic
product (GDP) for Latin America this year is between 4.2-4.3
precent, according to predictions made by international financial
organizations here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Inverlat, J.P. Morgan as well as the stock
brokerage Merrill Lynch, a strong increase in national consumption
and the world economic vigor will enable Latin America to become
one of the most dynamic regions in the world with economic growth
projected at more than 4 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Chile's National Fish Company inaugurated the
first odorless fish-drying system to make fishmeal in its San
Antonio plant.
</P>
<P>
The system, implemented by European and U.S. companies for
drying fishmeal via hot air, will completely eliminate bad smells.
</P>
<P>
This is the first system in Chile and Latin America with
a capacity to process 60 tons per hour.
</P>
<P>
Chile's fishmeal exports in 1996 totalled 1,005,771 tons
worth a total 656 million dollars. 
</P>
