<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Delegation Pays Respects to Richard Nixon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YORBA LINDA, CALIF., April 22 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese delegation
laid a wreath at Richard Nixon's memorial site here today in
observing the third anniversary of the late president's death.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in front of the late president's grave, Qi Huaiyuan,
head of the delegation and veteran diplomat, said that Nixon was
an outstanding statesman of the contemporary history with
foresight, courage and insight.
</P>
<P>
Nixon's historic China visit 25 years ago, which was made when
the two countries had been kept apart and antagonistic with each
other for a long time, was something extraordinary, said Qi,
former Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs and now president of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries
(CPAFFC).
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people will always remember him and his
contributions to developing the Sino-U.S. relations," Qi said.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the present relations between the two countries,
Qi said that although there have been ups and downs, development
is the trend.
</P>
<P>
Qi and his delegation visited the Richard Nixon Library and
Birthplace. They also toured the library's galleries and the
newest special exhibit, "Pacific Visions: Asia and the American
Presidency," an exhibition highlighting Nixon's role in the
opening of U.S. relations with China.
</P>
<P>
The CPAFFC's southern California visit was the final leg of its
four-city tour. While in the area, the delegation also visited La
Casa Pacifica in San Clemente, which served as the Western White
House during the Nixon Administration and is now a private home.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1954, CPAFFC aims at promoting cultural, economic
and education exchange between China and other nations. According
to the delegation, 100 American high school students will meet the
same number of Chinese students this summer in China to observe
the 25th anniversary of the signing of the Sino-U.S. Shanghai
Communique and discuss the relations between the two countries in
the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
